N2  - Abstract This paper describes a proposal for operating a centralized netting queue for nonurgent interbank payments that involves take-it-or-leave-it offers and allocates liquidity costs using the Shapley value. This method achieves fairness and ensures welfare-maximizing netting proposals are agreeable to all providers of liquidity.
